---
import BaseLayout from '../../components/layout/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="AI Visibility Audit | Editorial Intelligence"
  description="Understand how AI systems see your organisation, where your authority is weak, and what evidence, narratives and content structures could improve your visibility and credibility."
  ogDescription="Understand how AI systems see your organisation, where your authority is weak, and what evidence, narratives and content structures could improve your visibility and credibility."
>
  <article class="container-site py-20">
    <div class="ava-inner">

      <!-- Hero -->
      <header class="mb-16">
        <p class="t-label mb-6">AI Visibility Audit</p>
        <h1 class="t-display mb-6">Become a source AI systems can understand, trust and recommend.</h1>
        <div class="prose-section mb-8">
          <p>The AI Visibility Audit helps B2B organisations understand how they appear in AI-generated answers — and what is stopping them from becoming a recognised source in their market.</p>
          <p>It goes beyond technical optimisation to examine the evidence, expertise, narratives and connected knowledge that shape whether an organisation can be confidently understood and surfaced by AI systems.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-ctas">
          <a href="mailto:asavin@editorialintelligence.co?subject=AI%20Visibility%20Audit%20enquiry" class="ava-btn">Discuss an AI Visibility Audit</a>
          <a href="/frameworks/ai-search-visibility" class="ava-link">Read the AI search framework →</a>
        </div>
      </header>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Problem section -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="ava-h2 mb-6">AI visibility is not only a search problem</h2>
        <div class="prose-section mb-8">
          <p>Organisations are beginning to ask why competitors appear in ChatGPT, Perplexity, Google AI Overviews and other AI-generated answers while they do not.</p>
          <p>The immediate temptation is to treat this as another optimisation problem: publish more pages, add FAQs, adjust metadata or target more queries.</p>
          <p>Those actions may help, but they cannot compensate for an organisation whose knowledge is fragmented, generic or difficult to verify.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="ava-list mb-8">
          <li>Valuable research is published once and then disappears.</li>
          <li>Customer evidence is scattered across unrelated pages.</li>
          <li>Subject-matter expertise is not visible on the website.</li>
          <li>The organisation has content but no recognisable position.</li>
          <li>Important concepts are described inconsistently.</li>
          <li>Competitors have become more strongly associated with priority topics.</li>
          <li>Individual pages exist, but they do not form a connected body of knowledge.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="prose-note">The audit identifies the editorial and knowledge-system problems beneath the visibility problem.</p>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- What it answers -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="ava-h2 mb-4">What the audit helps you understand</h2>
        <p class="prose-intro mb-10">Six questions the audit is designed to answer.</p>
        <div class="answers-grid">

          <div class="answer-card">
            <span class="answer-num">01</span>
            <h3 class="answer-heading">How do AI systems currently describe you?</h3>
            <p class="answer-body">Review how the organisation is represented in relevant AI-generated answers, including recurring language, claims, omissions and inaccuracies.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="answer-card">
            <span class="answer-num">02</span>
            <h3 class="answer-heading">Which topics are you associated with?</h3>
            <p class="answer-body">Identify where the organisation has a visible relationship with priority commercial topics — and where competitors own the conversation.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="answer-card">
            <span class="answer-num">03</span>
            <h3 class="answer-heading">What evidence supports your authority?</h3>
            <p class="answer-body">Assess original research, customer evidence, expert commentary, frameworks, events, reports and other defensible sources.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="answer-card">
            <span class="answer-num">04</span>
            <h3 class="answer-heading">Where is your knowledge fragmented?</h3>
            <p class="answer-body">Find disconnected pages, inconsistent terminology, unsupported claims and evidence that is difficult for people or machines to navigate.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="answer-card">
            <span class="answer-num">05</span>
            <h3 class="answer-heading">What can competitors claim more credibly?</h3>
            <p class="answer-body">Compare the organisation's visible evidence and narrative position against a small set of relevant competitors.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="answer-card">
            <span class="answer-num">06</span>
            <h3 class="answer-heading">What should you improve first?</h3>
            <p class="answer-body">Prioritise practical changes across content, evidence, architecture, expertise and narrative development.</p>
          </div>

        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- What is assessed -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="ava-h2 mb-10">What the audit assesses</h2>

        <div class="assess-grid">

          <div class="assess-category">
            <h3 class="assess-heading">AI answer visibility</h3>
            <ul class="ava-list-sm">
              <li>Presence in relevant AI-generated answers</li>
              <li>Accuracy of company descriptions</li>
              <li>Topic and category association</li>
              <li>Citations and source patterns</li>
              <li>Competitor visibility</li>
              <li>Brand and product confusion</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="assess-category">
            <h3 class="assess-heading">Evidence strength</h3>
            <ul class="ava-list-sm">
              <li>Original research</li>
              <li>Customer evidence</li>
              <li>Case studies</li>
              <li>Data and proprietary insight</li>
              <li>Named experts</li>
              <li>External corroboration</li>
              <li>Clear sourcing</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="assess-category">
            <h3 class="assess-heading">Narrative distinctiveness</h3>
            <ul class="ava-list-sm">
              <li>Recognisable strategic positions</li>
              <li>Named concepts and frameworks</li>
              <li>Consistency of language</li>
              <li>Defensible claims</li>
              <li>Clear market point of view</li>
              <li>Evidence supporting each argument</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="assess-category">
            <h3 class="assess-heading">Knowledge architecture</h3>
            <ul class="ava-list-sm">
              <li>Connections between related content</li>
              <li>Topic clusters and pathways</li>
              <li>Internal linking</li>
              <li>Framework, narrative and evidence relationships</li>
              <li>Content discoverability</li>
              <li>Duplication and fragmentation</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="assess-category">
            <h3 class="assess-heading">Expertise signals</h3>
            <ul class="ava-list-sm">
              <li>Visible authorship</li>
              <li>Subject-matter expert participation</li>
              <li>Leadership perspectives</li>
              <li>Practitioner experience</li>
              <li>Author and organisation credibility</li>
              <li>Consistent expertise across channels</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="assess-category">
            <h3 class="assess-heading">Buyability</h3>
            <ul class="ava-list-sm">
              <li>Whether AI can explain what the organisation does</li>
              <li>Whether its differentiation is clear</li>
              <li>Whether proof supports commercial claims</li>
              <li>Whether use cases and audiences are explicit</li>
              <li>Whether the organisation is likely to be included in recommendations</li>
              <li>Whether visibility connects to a plausible buying decision</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

        </div>

        <p class="assess-note">Buyability assessment draws on the <a href="/frameworks/ai-visibility-buyability" class="ava-inline-link">AI Visibility and Buyability framework</a> — which explains how evidence-backed authority translates into commercial outcomes.</p>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- What the client receives -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="ava-h2 mb-4">What you leave with</h2>
        <p class="prose-intro mb-10">Six concrete deliverables, shaped around your market and available evidence.</p>

        <div class="deliverables-list">

          <div class="deliverable-item">
            <div class="deliverable-header">
              <span class="deliverable-num">01</span>
              <h3 class="deliverable-heading">AI visibility baseline</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="deliverable-body">A documented view of how selected AI systems currently represent the organisation across agreed priority questions.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="deliverable-item">
            <div class="deliverable-header">
              <span class="deliverable-num">02</span>
              <h3 class="deliverable-heading">Competitor comparison</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="deliverable-body">A focused comparison showing where competitors are more visible, more clearly positioned or better supported by evidence.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="deliverable-item">
            <div class="deliverable-header">
              <span class="deliverable-num">03</span>
              <h3 class="deliverable-heading">Evidence and authority map</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="deliverable-body">A map of the research, expertise, customer proof, frameworks and external signals currently supporting the organisation's authority.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="deliverable-item">
            <div class="deliverable-header">
              <span class="deliverable-num">04</span>
              <h3 class="deliverable-heading">Narrative gap analysis</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="deliverable-body">An assessment of the arguments the organisation wants to own, the claims it can currently support and the gaps preventing a coherent position.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="deliverable-item">
            <div class="deliverable-header">
              <span class="deliverable-num">05</span>
              <h3 class="deliverable-heading">Knowledge-system assessment</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="deliverable-body">A review of whether relevant content works as a connected body of knowledge or as a collection of isolated assets.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="deliverable-item">
            <div class="deliverable-header">
              <span class="deliverable-num">06</span>
              <h3 class="deliverable-heading">Prioritised 90-day roadmap</h3>
            </div>
            <p class="deliverable-body">A practical sequence of quick wins, foundational changes and longer-term opportunities.</p>
          </div>

        </div>

        <p class="scope-note">The exact scope is agreed before the audit and shaped around your market, priority topics and available evidence.</p>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Report structure -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="ava-h2 mb-8">What the final report covers</h2>
        <ol class="report-list">
          <li>Executive summary</li>
          <li>Current AI visibility baseline</li>
          <li>Priority query and topic findings</li>
          <li>Competitor comparison</li>
          <li>Evidence inventory</li>
          <li>Narrative and authority gaps</li>
          <li>Knowledge architecture findings</li>
          <li>Buyability findings</li>
          <li>Immediate improvements</li>
          <li>90-day roadmap</li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Who it is for -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="ava-h2 mb-4">Who this is for</h2>
        <p class="prose-intro mb-6">The audit is designed for B2B organisations whose credibility depends on being understood in complex or competitive markets.</p>
        <ul class="ava-list mb-6">
          <li>SaaS and enterprise technology companies</li>
          <li>Fintech and financial services organisations</li>
          <li>Professional services firms</li>
          <li>Research-led organisations</li>
          <li>Companies investing in thought leadership</li>
          <li>Organisations with significant customer, event or expert insight</li>
          <li>Startups entering an established category</li>
          <li>Scaleups trying to define or own a market position</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="prose-note">It is particularly useful when you already have substantial content or evidence but cannot see it translating into authority, visibility or differentiation.</p>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Who typically commissions -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="ava-h2 mb-6">Who typically commissions the work</h2>
        <ul class="ava-list-sm-plain">
          <li>Chief marketing officers</li>
          <li>Content and editorial leaders</li>
          <li>Thought leadership teams</li>
          <li>Corporate communications teams</li>
          <li>Product marketing leaders</li>
          <li>Research and insights teams</li>
          <li>Customer marketing leaders</li>
          <li>Founders and marketing leaders at startups and scaleups</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- What this is not -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="ava-h2 mb-8">What this audit is not</h2>
        <div class="not-grid">

          <div class="not-item">
            <h3 class="not-heading">Not a ranking guarantee</h3>
            <p class="not-body">AI-generated answers vary by system, prompt, geography, personalisation and time. The audit does not promise a fixed position or guaranteed citation.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="not-item">
            <h3 class="not-heading">Not only a technical SEO audit</h3>
            <p class="not-body">Technical accessibility matters, but this service focuses primarily on knowledge quality, evidence, expertise, narrative and content structure.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="not-item">
            <h3 class="not-heading">Not a volume-content plan</h3>
            <p class="not-body">The recommendation will not automatically be to publish more. It may be to connect, strengthen, consolidate or better evidence what already exists.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="not-item">
            <h3 class="not-heading">Not prompt manipulation</h3>
            <p class="not-body">The goal is not to find temporary tricks for influencing individual outputs. It is to improve the underlying authority and clarity of the organisation.</p>
          </div>

        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- EI connection -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="ava-h2 mb-6">Why Editorial Intelligence</h2>
        <div class="prose-section mb-6">
          <p>AI systems are better able to understand organisations whose knowledge is connected, evidenced and distinctively their own.</p>
          <p>Editorial Intelligence provides the underlying method: identifying useful signals, interpreting what they mean, developing defensible narratives and connecting evidence into a body of knowledge that compounds over time.</p>
          <p>The AI Visibility Audit applies that method to a specific commercial question: can AI systems confidently understand what your organisation knows, why it is credible and when it should be recommended?</p>
        </div>
        <div class="ei-links">
          <a href="/intelligence" class="ei-link">What is Editorial Intelligence →</a>
          <a href="/editorial-intelligence-os" class="ei-link">Editorial Intelligence OS →</a>
          <a href="/frameworks/ai-search-visibility" class="ei-link">AI search framework →</a>
          <a href="/frameworks/ai-visibility-buyability" class="ei-link">AI Visibility and Buyability →</a>
          <a href="/narratives/hidden-hours" class="ei-link">Hidden Hours — in practice →</a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Process -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="ava-h2 mb-8">How the audit works</h2>
        <div class="process-steps">

          <div class="process-step">
            <span class="process-num">1</span>
            <div class="process-content">
              <h3 class="process-heading">Define the territory</h3>
              <p class="process-body">Agree the priority audiences, commercial topics, competitors and questions the organisation wants to be associated with.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="process-step">
            <span class="process-num">2</span>
            <div class="process-content">
              <h3 class="process-heading">Test current visibility</h3>
              <p class="process-body">Review how selected AI systems answer those questions and which organisations, sources and evidence appear.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="process-step">
            <span class="process-num">3</span>
            <div class="process-content">
              <h3 class="process-heading">Audit the knowledge system</h3>
              <p class="process-body">Assess the organisation's evidence, narratives, expertise, content relationships and commercial clarity.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="process-step">
            <span class="process-num">4</span>
            <div class="process-content">
              <h3 class="process-heading">Set the roadmap</h3>
              <p class="process-body">Present the findings, prioritise the changes and identify what can be improved over the following 90 days.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Founding offer -->
      <section class="founding-section mb-16">
        <h2 class="founding-heading mb-4">Founding audit engagements</h2>
        <div class="prose-section mb-6">
          <p>I am currently opening a limited number of founding AI Visibility Audit engagements for B2B organisations.</p>
          <p>These early engagements will receive the full audit methodology and a prioritised roadmap, with scope shaped collaboratively around the organisation's most important market questions.</p>
          <p>In return, I will ask for direct feedback on the usefulness of the process and, where appropriate, permission to document an anonymised or attributed case study.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="mailto:asavin@editorialintelligence.co?subject=AI%20Visibility%20Audit%20enquiry" class="ava-btn">Discuss a founding audit</a>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- FAQ -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="ava-h2 mb-8">Frequently asked questions</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">Which AI systems do you assess?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>The exact mix is agreed according to the market and the organisation's priority audiences. It may include systems such as ChatGPT, Google's AI experiences and Perplexity, depending on where your buyers are most likely to encounter AI-generated answers. The audit does not rely on access to private model data or internal systems.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">Can you guarantee that we will appear in AI answers?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>No. AI-generated outputs vary by system, prompt, geography, personalisation and time, and cannot be guaranteed by any outside party. The audit improves the underlying signals that make an organisation easier to understand, verify and recommend — which is the condition for sustained visibility, not a shortcut to it.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">Is this the same as SEO?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>It overlaps with search in some areas — content architecture, technical accessibility and topical coverage all matter. But this service focuses more heavily on evidence quality, expertise signals, narrative consistency and how well an organisation's knowledge holds together as a connected body. Those are editorial and knowledge-system questions, not primarily technical ones.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">Do we need a large content library?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>No. A smaller body of original, well-connected and credible material can be more useful than a large volume of generic content. The audit assesses what you have, not how much of it there is.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">Will you implement the recommendations?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Implementation support can be scoped separately, including narrative development, evidence mapping, content architecture or editorial-system work. The audit is a complete engagement in itself; further work is available but not required.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">Is this suitable for startups?</summary>
            <div class="faq-answer">
              <p>Yes, particularly where a startup needs to establish category association, clarify differentiation or turn founder and customer insight into visible authority. The audit can help identify what evidence exists and what needs to be built. It should not be positioned as a substitute for product-market fit — clarity about what the organisation does comes before visibility.</p>
            </div>
          </details>

        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Final CTA -->
      <section class="mb-8">
        <h2 class="ava-h2 mb-4">Find out what AI can — and cannot — confidently say about your organisation.</h2>
        <div class="prose-section mb-8">
          <p>Use the audit to establish your current visibility, identify the authority gaps beneath it and create a practical plan for becoming a more credible and recommendable source.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="final-ctas">
          <a href="mailto:asavin@editorialintelligence.co?subject=AI%20Visibility%20Audit%20enquiry" class="ava-btn">Discuss an AI Visibility Audit</a>
          <a href="/frameworks/ai-search-visibility" class="ava-link">Explore the AI search framework →</a>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .ava-inner {
    max-width: 42rem;
  }

  /* ── Prose ── */
  .prose-section {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .prose-section p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
  }

  .prose-intro {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
  }

  .prose-note {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* ── Headings ── */
  .ava-h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(1.15rem, 2.5vw, 1.4rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  /* ── CTAs ── */
  .hero-ctas,
  .final-ctas {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .ava-btn {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    background: var(--color-accent);
    color: var(--color-surface);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    font-weight: 600;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.25rem;
    border-radius: 3px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: opacity 0.15s;
  }

  .ava-btn:hover { opacity: 0.85; }

  .ava-link {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color 0.15s;
  }

  .ava-link:hover { color: var(--color-accent); }

  .ava-inline-link {
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 35%, transparent);
    padding-bottom: 1px;
    transition: opacity 0.15s;
  }

  .ava-inline-link:hover { opacity: 0.8; }

  /* ── Lists ── */
  .ava-list {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .ava-list li {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .ava-list li::before {
    content: '→';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .ava-list-sm {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.4rem;
  }

  .ava-list-sm li {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
    padding-left: 1rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .ava-list-sm li::before {
    content: '·';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .ava-list-sm-plain {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    columns: 2;
  }

  .ava-list-sm-plain li {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
    break-inside: avoid;
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .ava-list-sm-plain {
      columns: 1;
    }
  }

  /* ── What the audit answers (6-card grid) ── */
  .answers-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 1px;
    background: var(--color-rule);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-radius: 4px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  @media (min-width: 540px) {
    .answers-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    }
  }

  .answer-card {
    background: var(--color-surface-secondary);
    padding: 1.25rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .answer-num {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.5625rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    opacity: 0.7;
  }

  .answer-heading {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .answer-body {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
